4 HR____ CELEBRATING THE ACCOMPLISHMENTS OF CATHY MITCHELL
5 UPON THE OCCASION OF HER RETIREMENT.
6
7 WHEREAS, it is with profound appreciation and deepest
8 admiration that we celebrate Cathy Mitchell for 24 years of
9 distinguished public service and steadfast commitment to the
10 residents of Scottsboro and Jackson County through her work
11 as Executive Director at the IMPACT Learning Center; we also
12 take this opportunity to heartily congratulate her upon her
13 retirement, effective in January 2026; and
14 WHEREAS, Cathy has dedicated her life's work to
15 improving the lives of others, especially children; she
16 helped to expand educational opportunities across Jackson
17 County through strengthening community partnerships between
18 nonprofit organizations, schools, and families; and
19 WHEREAS, the majority of Cathy's adult professional
20 life has been devoted to service at the IMPACT (Individually
21 Managing Personal Achievement & Career Training) Learning
22 Center; she began as a Network Coordinator, establishing and
23 supervising the first pre-K classes in both Jackson County
24 and the City of Scottsboro; her leadership efforts
25 contributed directly to both school systems establishing
26 successful public pre-K programs; and
27 WHEREAS, through IMPACT, Cathy initiated and
28 supported numerous educational enrichment programs,
Page 1

supported numerous educational enrichment programs,
HR168 INTRODUCED
29 including adult computer classes; ACT preparation classes;
30 resume preparation assistance for adults; "Choices" classes
31 for sixth-graders which encouraged school retention; Liberty
32 Learning citizen enrichment classes for second-, fifth-, and
33 seventh-graders; and STEM Family Activity Nights at local
34 schools; and
35 WHEREAS, Cathy also helped establish the Dolly Parton
36 Imagination Library for Jackson County, resulting in the
37 delivery of approximately 70,000 books to children ages five
38 and under in just three years; she facilitated Ron Clark
39 training for teachers, who in turn trained additional
40 educators, expanding instructional impact throughout the
41 county; and Cathy consistently worked to improve educational
42 access and opportunities for children and adults throughout
43 Jackson County; and
44 WHEREAS, her work in the community extends to Nourish
45 One Child, a local nonprofit providing weekend food
46 assistance to children in the City of Scottsboro; as an
47 active board member, Cathy is instrumental in organizing and
48 helping establish Food for Thought for children in Jackson
49 County; she is also actively involved in fundraising
50 efforts, including Dragon Races and grant writing
51 initiatives; and
52 WHEREAS, other community involvement includes service
53 as a board member for the Jackson County United Givers Fund
54 and longtime membership in the Three Arts Club, a local
55 women's charity organization supporting arts education in
56 Scottsboro City Schools; Cathy is also an active member of
Page 2

Scottsboro City Schools; Cathy is also an active member of
